<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Resolving constraint violations when width is less than min-width and height is less than min-height, where min-width/width equals min-height/height</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#min-max-widths" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Resolved width is min(max-width,min-height * width/height) and resolved height is min-height when width is less than min-width and height is less than min-height, where min-width/width equals min-height/height." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 1in;
                min-width: 2in;
                height: 1in;
                min-height: 3in;
                background-color: green;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 2in;
                height: 3in;
                background-color: blue;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the green box is the same size as the blue box.</p>
        <div id="d1"></div>
        <div id="d2"></div>
    </body>
</html>